        "title": "IntelliJ: use docker jvm or docker maven?",
        "body": "<p>I have a docker/jvm instance, which I use from the command line to compile and run java code. IntelliJ's project config requires me to point at a jvm on the filesystem. <\/p>\n\n<p>So, I was wondering, can I configure intellij to use this docker container? I suppose I could configure a docker container, keep it running, and mount/share its filesystem, but I don't want that -- I want to use my ephemeral container instance.<\/p>\n\n<p>I have the same idea for using maven -- can I use a docker instance of maven without mounting the filesystem, from within intellij? Again, intellij seems to require a pointer to a filesystem location for maven, so this seems problematic.<\/p>\n\n<p>Does anyone have any clue if this is possible, or how to go about configuring such a thing?<\/p>\n",
        "question_id": 36429949,
